  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Aqudel (Alghollthu Prodigy)",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Vidileths",
              "aonid": 2813,
              "game-obj": "Monsters",
              "name": "Vidileths",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "alghollthu",
              "aonid": 358,
              "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
              "name": "alghollthu",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Alghollthu Hierarchy",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 22,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Vidileths are the leaders of the alghollthu, subtly influencing events to foster what they consider the most favorable outcome, and some of their plots are centuries in the making. They control vast networks of their kin, directing them to influence lower alghollthu and leverage their knowledge to manipulate lesser beings than themselves (which is how they see all others). Aqudels and nymoluses fill the role of mid-ranking administrators, taking orders from veiled masters and then enacting their plans with resources derived from their own networks. An aqudel might supervise only one small cell, while a nymolus might oversee a dozen.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 22,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Aqudels are obsessed with control. They consider everything around them open to manipulation, and their position in the alghollthu hierarchy leads them to lord over networks of ugothols or small, established societies that they often bully and exploit from the shadows. Aqudels answer only to vidileths, following their commands with a combination of simpering compliance and scheming distrust.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
        "aonid": 276,
        "game-obj": "Sources",
        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 22",
        "type": "link"
      },
      "name": "Monster Core 2",
      "page": 22,
      "type": "source"
    }
  ],
